AKURE – Ondo State Health Commissioner, Dr Wahab Adegbenro is dead. According to VANGUARD Newspapers, reports from government quarters said he died of COVID-19, aged 65. Wahab Oluropo Adegbenro was born on 5th June 1955 at Ilara-mokin in Ifedore Local Government Area of Ondo State. He holds the Bachelor of Medicine, Bachelor of Surgery (M.B; B.S). Dr. Adegbenro established Crown Hospital, Akure where he was the Chief Medical Director. SundiataPost recalls that Ondo State Governor Rotimi Akeredolu on Tuesday, announced that he tested positive for coronavirus. By Segun Giwa Akure - The Olowa of Igbara-Oke Kingdom, Oba Francis Agbede, has called on residents of Ondo State to take preventive measures against the coronavirus. Agbede made the call on Saturday when he played host to the State Taskforce on COVID-19 on a sensitisation visit to his palace… March 28, 2020 In "News" Ondo state has recorded its first COVID-19 death. The state Commissioner for Health, Dr Wahab Adegbenro, who disclosed this to newsmen, said the patient died in the early hours of today Monday May 11 at the Infectious Disease Hospital on Igbatoro Road in Akure, the state capital. Currently, 15 cases… May 11, 2020 In "News" By Olusola Oke Akure -  The Ondo State Government has advised the people of the state to be proactive in containing the reported cases of yellow fever across the country. Dr Wahab Adegbenro, the state Commissioner for Health, gave the advice in a statement on Thursday in Akure. According to… November 29, 2018 In "Health"